Adeniyi Olugbemi, Sokoto The Sokoto State chapter of the All Progressives Congress, has inaugurated the State Caretaker Executive Committee as well as the caretaker chairmen for the 23 Local Government areas. Speaking at the event, in Sokoto, on Sunday, the state party leader, Senator Aliyu Wamakko, felicitated with the new leaders. Wamakko, who represents Sokoto North Senatorial District in the Senate, said the party was delighted with their commitment to its ideals hence the decision to reappoint them on caretaker basis as it prepares to begin its process of rebuilding. He said, “I am once again thanking clerics, traders, traditional rulers, women and youths’ groups, in this direction.” Also speaking, the Minister of Police Affairs, Alhaji Muhammadu Dingyadi, while commanding Wamakko’s leadership said, “Without him, without his support and encouragement, we would not have recorded the tremendous achievements we have made.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com